e Minister of Norway]] (d. 1925)\n*[[1858]] &ndash; [[Liberty Hyde Bailey]], American botanist and academic, co-founded the [[American Society for Horticultural Science]] (d. 1954)\n*[[1860]] &ndash; [[Waldemar Haffkine]], Russian-Swiss bacteriologist and microbiologist (d. 1930)\n*[[1864]] &ndash; [[Johan Halvorsen]], Norwegian violinist, composer, and conductor ([[Oslo Philharmonic]]) (d. 1935)\n*[[1865]] &ndash; [[Manuk Abeghian]], Armenian author and scholar (d. 1944)\n*[[1866]] &ndash; [[Matthew Charlton]], Australian miner and politician (d. 1948)\n*  1866   &ndash; [[Johan Vaaler]], Norwegian inventor, often erroneously identified as the inventor of the [[Paper clip]] (d. 1910)\n*[[1868]] &ndash; [[Grace Chisholm Young]], English mathematician (d. 1944)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.agnesscott.edu/lriddle/women/young.htm|title=Grace Chisholm Young|publisher=[[Agnes Scott College]]|access-date=Dec 27, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[1869]] &ndash; [[Stanis\u0142aw Wojciechowski]], Polish scholar and politician, 2nd [[List of heads of state of Poland|President of the Republic of Poland]] (d. 1953)\n*[[1874]] &ndash; [[Eug\u00e8ne Fiset]], Canadian physician, general, and politician, 18th [[Lieutenant Governor of Quebec]] (d. 1951)\n*  1874   &ndash; [[Harold L. Ickes]], American journalist and politician, 32nd [[United States Secretary of the Interior]] (d. 1952)\n*[[1878]] &ndash; [[Reza Shah]], Iranian king (d. 1944)\n*[[1886]] &ndash; [[Wladimir Burliuk]], Ukrainian-Greek painter and illustrator (d. 1917)\n*[[1887]] &ndash; [[Marjorie Merriweather Post]], American businesswoman and philanthropist, founded [[General Foods]] (d. 1973)\n*  1887   &ndash; [[L\u00fctfi K\u0131rdar]], Turkish physician and politician, [[Ministry of Health (Turkey)|Turkish Minister of Health]] (d. 1961)\n*[[1879]] &ndash; [[Benjamin R. Jacobs]], American biochemist (d. 1963)<ref>''Announcements'', ''[[Science (journal)|Science]]'', New Series, volume 139, number 3557, pp.&nbsp;818\u2013819, March 1963</ref>\n*[[1890]] &ndash; [[Boris Delaunay]], Russian mathematician and mountaineer (d. 1980)\n*[[1892]] &ndash; [[James Basevi Ord]], Mexican-American colonel (d. 1938)\n*[[1897]] &ndash; [[Jackson Scholz]], American runner (d. 1986)\n*[[1900]] &ndash; [[Gilberto Freyre]], Brazilian sociologist, anthropologist, historian and writer (d. 1987)\n*[[1904]] &ndash; [[George Brent]], Irish-American actor (d. 1979)\n*  1904   &ndash; [[J. Pat O'Malley]], English-American actor (d. 1985)\n*[[1905]] &ndash; [[Berthold Schenk Graf von Stauffenberg]], German lawyer and judge (d. 1944)\n*[[1907]] &ndash; [[Zarah Leander]], Swedish actress and singer (d. 1981)\n*[[1909]] &ndash; [[Jaroslava Muchov\u00e1|Jaroslava Muchov\u00e1 Syllabov\u00e1]], Czech painter (d. 1986)\n*[[1912]] &ndash; [[Lightnin' Hopkins]], American blues singer-songwriter and guitarist (d. 1982)\n*[[1912]] &ndash; [[Louis Paul Boon]], Flemish journalist and author (d. 1979)\n*[[1913]] &ndash; [[Macdonald Carey]], American actor (d. 1994)\n*  1913   &ndash; [[Jack Fairman]], English race car driver (d. 2002)\n*[[1916]] &ndash; [[Frank Coghlan, Jr.]], American actor and pilot (d. 2009)\n*  1916   &ndash; [[Fadil Hoxha]], Kosovar commander and politician, 2nd [[President of Kosovo]] (d. 2001)\n*  1916   &ndash; [[Harry James]], American trumpet player, bandleader, and actor (d. 1983)\n*[[1918]] &ndash; [[Richard Ellmann]], American author and critic (d. 1987)\n*  1918   &ndash; [[Punch Imlach]], Canadian ice hockey player, coach, and manager (d. 1987)\n*[[1919]] &ndash; [[Lawrence Tierney]], American actor (d. 2002)\n*[[1920]] &ndash; [[E. Donnall Thomas]], American physician and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2012)\n*[[1921]] &ndash; [[Madelyn Pugh]], American television writer and producer (d. 2011)\n*[[1922]] &ndash; [[Eddie Calvert]], English trumpeter (d. 1978)\n*[[1926]] &ndash; [[Ben Johnston (composer)|Ben Johnston]], American composer and academic  (d. 2019)\n*  1926   &ndash; [[Norm Van Brocklin]], American football player and coach (d. 1983)\n*[[1927]] &ndash; [[Christian Marquand]], French actor, director, and screenwriter (d. 2000)\n*  1927   &ndash; [[Carl Smith (country musician)|Carl Smith]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (d. 2010)\n*[[1928]] &ndash; [[Bob Wilber]], American clarinetist and saxophonist (d. 2019)\n*[[1930]] &ndash; [[Zhores Alferov]], Belarusian-Russian physicist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 2019)<ref>{{cite book|author1=Benediktas Juodka|author2=V. P. Puronas|title=The Lithuanian Academy of Sciences|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CuYjAQAAIAAJ|year=2003|publisher=Lietuvos moksl\u0173 akademija|isbn=978-9986-08-038-1|page=169}}</ref>\n*[[1932]] &ndash; [[Alan Bean]], American captain, pilot, and astronaut (d. 2018)\n*  1932   &ndash; [[Arif Mardin]], Turkish-American record producer (d. 2006)\n*[[1933]] &ndash; [[Ruth Bader Ginsburg]], American lawyer and judge\n*  1933   &ndash; [[Philippe de Broca]], French actor, director, and screenwriter (d. 2004)\n*[[1934]] &ndash; [[Richard Layard, Baron Layard]], English economist and academic\n*  1934   &ndash; [[Kanshi Ram]], Indian politician (d. 2006)\n*[[1935]] &ndash; [[David Andrews (politician)|David Andrews]], Irish politician, 21st [[Minister for Foreign Affairs and Trade|Minister of Foreign Affairs for Ireland]]\n*  1935   &ndash; [[Judd Hirsch]], American actor\n*  1935   &ndash; [[Afsar Ahmad Siddiqui]], Bangladeshi politician (d. 2001)\n*  1935   &ndash; [[Jimmy Swaggart]], American pastor and television host\n*  1935   &ndash; [[Leonid Yengibarov]], Russian-Armenian clown and boxer (d. 1972)\n*[[1936]] &ndash; [[Howard Greenfield]], American songwriter (d. 1986)\n*[[1937]] &ndash; [[Marcus Raichle]], American neurologist and physiologist\n*  1937   &ndash; [[Valentin Rasputin]], Russian environmentalist and author (d. 2015)\n*[[1938]] &ndash; [[Charles Lloyd (jazz musician)|Charles Lloyd]], American saxophonist and flute player\n*[[1939]] &ndash; [[Ted Kaufman]], American engineer and politician\n*  1939   &ndash; [[Robert Nye]], English author, poet, and playwright (d. 2016)\n*  1939   &ndash; [[Julie Tullis]], English mountaineer (d. 1986)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/10.1093/ref:odnb/9780198614128.001.0001/odnb-9780198614128-e-62486;jsessionid=E915EA79174CEB7198C992A9BC82A948|title=Tullis [n\u00e9e Palau], Julia Elissa May [Julie]|work=[[Oxford Dictionary of National Biography]]|access-date=Dec 27, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[Frank Dobson]], English politician, [[Secretary of State for Health]] (d. 2019)\n*  1940   &ndash; [[Phil Lesh]], American bassist\n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[Mike Love]], American singer-songwriter and musician\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Carolyn Hansson]], Canadian materials engineer<ref>{{cite web |title=WOMEN OF IMPACT |url=https://www.metsoc.org/women-impact/ |website=metsoc.org |accessdate=December 27, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171030050306/https://www.metsoc.org/women-impact/ |archivedate=October 30, 2017}}</ref> \n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[David Cronenberg]], Canadian actor, director, and screenwriter\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Lynda La Plante]], English actress, screenwriter, and author\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Michael Scott-Joynt]], English bishop (d. 2014)\n*  1943   &ndash; [[Sly Stone]], American singer-songwriter, musician, and producer\n*  1943   &ndash; [[The Iron Sheik]], Iranian-American wrestler and actor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/bios/i/iron-sheik/|title=Iron Sheik|website=onlineworldofwrestling.com|access-date=Dec 27, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[Chi Cheng (athlete)|Chi Cheng]], Taiwanese runner and politician\n*  1944   &ndash; [[Jacques Doillon]], French director and screenwriter\n*  1944   &ndash; [[Francis Mankiewicz]], Canadian director, producer, and screenwriter (d. 1993)\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[A. K. Faezul Huq]], Bangladeshi lawyer and politician (d. 2007)\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Mark J. Green]], American lawyer and politician\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Bobby Bonds]], American baseball player and coach (d. 2003)\n*  1946   &ndash; [[John Dempsey (footballer, born 1946)|John Dempsey]], English born Irish international footballer, centre-back and manager<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=2003|title=John Dempsey|access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Ry Cooder]], American singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer\n*  1947   &ndash; [[Gino Ferrin]], German footballer and manager\n*  1947   &ndash; [[Juraj Kukura]], Slovak-German actor<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0474400/bio?ref_=nm_ov_bio_sm|title=Juraj Kukura|website=[[IMDb]]|access-date=Dec 27, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Kate Bornstein]], American author and activist<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n93121104.html|title=LC Linked Data Service: Authorities and Vocabularies (Library of Congress)|website=id.loc.gov|others=The Library of Congress|access-date=2018-03-05}}</ref>\n*  1948   &ndash; [[S\u00e9rgio Vieira de Mello]], Brazilian diplomat (d. 2003)\n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Olsen Brothers|J\u00f8rgen Olsen]], Danish singer-songwriter\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Kurt Koch]], Swiss cardinal\n*[[1951]] &ndash; [[David Alton, Baron Alton of Liverpool]], English educator and politician\n*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Howard Devoto]], English singer-songwriter \n*  1952   &ndash; [[Philip Green]], English businessman\n*  1952   &ndash; [[Howard Koh]], American physician and politician, 14th [[United States Assistant Secretary for Health]]\n*[[1953]] &ndash; [[Richard Bruton]], Irish economist and politician, [[Minister for Jobs, Enterprise and Innovation]]\n*  1953   &ndash; [[Heather Graham Pozzessere]], American author\n*  1953   &ndash; [[Kumba Ial\u00e1]], Bissau-Guinean educator and politician, [[List of heads of state of Guinea-Bissau|President of Guinea-Bissau]] (d. 2014)\n*[